<HR WIDTH=240></HR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulildian5.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lildian5</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/10/02 6:58:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3286.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What level for Othmir?</span><hr size=1> My guildie started at I think 54, might have been 53. He still cant do it w/o help from his lumi- but if you have one i think you can head there a bit earlier = ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unerill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nerill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/10/02 12:53:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3286.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/ezcrash1/nerillpic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What level for Othmir?</span><hr size=1> Quadding: I started poaching the water rats at level 54. I did in fact NEED my Lumi Staff to finish them off. My Wisdom was 199.<br>
<br>
Root/DOT: No problems root/dotting these at 54. No Lumi Staff needed. Winged Death is a wonderful spell :) <p><img src=http://members.home.net/ezcrash1/nerillsig.jpg HEIGHT=215 WIDTH=350></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unallowindawnfeather.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NallowinDawnfeather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/14/02 3:04:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3286.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What level for Othmir?</span><hr size=1> You can do these at level 52.<br>
<br>
Go to the camp closest to the cave to SG and use harmony to grab single spawns. Only go after the warriors at this level since shamans gate back when they get low and if there are any more mobs there you will soon be dead.  <br>
<br>
Othmir do not like wolf form so in my case (wood elf) i was safer with just sow.  I would strongly suggest hunting ulthorks first to get faction up before taking these guys on. One they drop tusks for a gem quest and when you are not kos you do not have to worry about the beachcombers. <br>
<br>
Breath of Ro and ES Vambraces as well as rooting will let me kill 3 of the warriors out of 4 before respawning. I have around 210 wisdom.  <br>
<br>
The shamans probably would not be so bad if you can quad them, if i remember right they should just continue with the pack rather then gate back so you can kill them.<br>
<br>
Key to soloing individual othmirs is harmony, learn it, use it, love it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Nallowin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaleficsz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>maleficSZ</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/17/02 12:21:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3286.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What level for Othmir?</span><hr size=1> WARNING: ONCE YOU COMMIT TO LEVELING ON OTHMIR, YOU WILL RUIN YOUR FACTION TO DO LODIZAL QUESTS!!!  With the +20wis shield quest in Luclin and considering how small a chance you actually have at getting a lodizal spawn its not a big deal to me =)<br>
<br>
At lv54 with 213 wis and ~+300 mana from my equipment (I'm not in a guild btw, just earned it from selling/trading/porting) , I can easily quad these at 54 using only 80% of my mana bar.  Before pulling these make sure to have Levitate &amp; Chloroplast up (regrowth isnt worth the extra 100m cause you shouldnt take too much damage)..use harmony on the shamans and 1 or 2 warriors so you pull 1 or 2 warriors at a time.  Snare 1 warrior to pull then snare dance the other one..then come back soon before harmony wears off on shaman to pull another 2.  I pull them up to the plateau area where the wyverns spawn and quad them north to south along the rocks.  While you are bunching them up, feel free to toss on the mana free DOT from ES arms as this helps with replacing damage lost to partial resists.  I'd recommend paying/trading for a c2 or c3 to reduce downtime and its great xp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uorangerobot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orangerobot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/20/02 12:25:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3286.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What level for Othmir?</span><hr size=1> Just another data point: 56 druid, 223 WIS, little or no MANA + items. I come up about 2 nukes short from taking these cute little buggers out on a kite. I can easily knock them out after a couple rounds of med kiting or DoTing with ES vams though. If I had a lumi it would be cake. Med kiting sort of sucks in my book but they seem to be noticably better exp than raptors and they drop money, gems, and crusty armor so I'll probably give up on the raptors now.<br>
<br>
Mitten <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upaldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Paldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/20/02 8:10:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3286.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What level for Othmir?</span><hr size=1> Also remember that the egress point in Cobalt Scar is dead center of the Othmir camp. <p><table width="85%" border="0">
